  "title": "M&E Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p>1.   Responsible for the co-ordination and interface with LTA System Wide Contractor and Department Heads</p><p>2.   Co-ordinate with Client and respective personnel / LTA System Wide Contractor on the co-ordination of construction and consolidate the action items and report back to Department Heads</p><p>3.   Preparing the co-ordinated installation programme (CIP) and sign off by all parties</p><p>4.   Manage the integration of the E&M SWC designs into the civil / structural / architectural designs ensuring authorities requirements are met</p><p>5.   Responsible for the application of permit and liaise with respective local Authorities on issues pertaining to permit for commencement of works / diversion of existing services</p><p>6.   Plan, Prepare and Update the schedule for the submission of Samples / Shop Drawings / Method Statement</p><p>7.   Raise CSD / SEM Changes queries in the event of services clashing. Prepare and Obtain approval for Final CSD / SEM drawings and sign off SWCs prior to construction.</p><p>8.   Assist Coordination manager to issue all the construction drawings and approved Sign Off drawings to related station/tunnel for construction and for preparing M&E procurement schedule and update periodically</p><p>9.   Required to attend co-ordination / progress / technical meetings</p><p>10.  Scheduling of overall M&E services works and review construction programme</p><p>11.  Coordinate with M&E Supervisors for the preparation of as-built information and submit to SWC Coordinator for his review</p><p>12.  Prepare and schedule for coordinated programme for M&E works</p><p>13.  Coordinate with M&E Supervisors for the preparation of as-built information and submit to SWC Coordinator for his review</p><p>14.  Carry out weekly site inspection and report progress, quality, specifications, protection and problems.</p><p>15.  Prepare M&E coordination drawings and liaise with Architectural Coordinators and Design Engineers to issue\ndrawing for approval.</p><p>16.  Responsible for managing a team of M&E coordinators and BIM Modelers in the design and coordination works;</p><p>17.  Interfacing or M&E planning, coordination with consultants and document control such as monitoring of sample submission, approval status of drawing</p><p>18.  Coordinating, organizing and preparing construction and Interfacing/M&E documents and drawing</p><p>19.  Ensure M&E works are carried out according to specifications / drawings;</p><p>20.  Inform Project Director / Project Manager on any technical / site problems</p><p>21.  Supervise the progress of works on site;</p><p>22.  Coordination of sub-contractor's work and ensuring the work is on schedule.</p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong><br />1. Degree or Diploma in Mechanical Engineering</p><p>2. Minimum 5 years’ relevant experience as E&M coordinator in large scale projects,\nMRT project (LTA).</p><p>3.   Highly motivated and independent with excellent team spirit and communication skills</p><p>4.   Good interpersonal and communication skill</p><p>5.   Good time management skill and able to work under pressure</p>",
